mpr_subject: User Credentials Required for App Store Review.
details:
Our latest IPA is in review on the App Store. However, we are facing issues because the provided user credentials do not have sufficient data to showcase the app’s functionality effectively.
To ensure a smooth review and approval process, we need to provide Apple with a test user that has comprehensive data. Please take the following actions:
Create/Identify a Test User – Ensure the account has enough data to demonstrate all key features of the app.
Verify Functional Coverage – The test user should be able to showcase workflows,  and other functionalities.
Share  Credentials – Provide the new test login details along with any necessary instructions or test scenarios.
Please prioritize this and share the updated credentials ASAP so we can avoid delays in the approval process.

Summary page 
TAb 1- Overview
Widget-1 - Welcome card,
Widget-2 - Attendance
Widget-3 - Day planner
Widget -4 - My Appointments
Widget -5 - My Task
Widget -6 - Quick Links
Widget -7 -RSS feeds

mpr_subject: User Credentials Required for App Store Review.
details:
Our latest IPA is in review on the App Store. However, we are facing issues because the provided user credentials do not have sufficient data to showcase the app’s functionality effectively.
To ensure a smooth review and approval process, we need to provide Apple with a test user that has comprehensive data. Please take the following actions:
Create/Identify a Test User – Ensure the account has enough data to demonstrate all key features of the app.
Verify Functional Coverage – The test user should be able to showcase workflows,  and other functionalities.
Share  Credentials – Provide the new test login details along with any necessary instructions or test scenarios.
Please prioritize this and share the updated credentials ASAP so we can avoid delays in the approval process.

mpr_subject: Modification of RCA options
details:
The Incident Layout has a field called "Root Cause" under RCA Details (Refer to the attached screenshot). The values in this field need to be changed to have uniform RCA codes that can be shared with customers. Those RCA fields are more from a production environment perspective than an Engineering perspective.
Existing fields need to be deleted, and the following fields need to be added, first in the test environment and then in production.

Application Defect
Incorrect Configuration
Application Limitation	
Documentation Bug	
Data Issue Due to Application	
Third-Party Libraries	
System Capacity Issues	
Database Maintenance	
User Error	
Wrong Deployment	
Environment - Network	
Environment - OS/Runtime	
Environment - Compute Resources	
Enivronment - Space / Storage	
Hardware
Third-Party Integrations	
Third-Party Software	
Database Issues	
Data Issue not due to Application
Expected Functionality	
New Requirement	
Undetermined
subject: Modification of RCA options

mpr_subject: MY- Azure Integration - Out Of TAT
details:
Out Of TAT-

Awaiting Input>30 days
Resolved with SA>30 Days

 Process of auto closure of non actioned case by delivery should be auto updated in azure:Either state should be closed or any other should be synced in azure from MY
We are implementing a process to automatically close cases in the following statuses to help clean up old and inactive data except Production cases:
Invalid

Configuration Issue
Is a Feature
Not a Bug
Awaiting Inputs
Workaround Provided
Without timely action, these cases accumulate over time and impact overall tracking and reporting. Once a case is closed through this process, it will no longer be eligible for Reopen or transition to any other status. If further action is required, ESG will need to raise a new case.
Below is the escalation matrix for this closure process:
After Week 4:
The case will be closed automatically, and a notification email will be sent to the case creator, the case creator’s manager, and the portfolio owner.
subject: MY- Azure Integration - Out Of TAT

details:
Hi Team,

We have received an issue reported by the AU Finance client stating that users are not able to download the case report. This issue has been observed after the last maintenance activity carried out on 09-Dec-2025.

As discussed, we request you to please:

1.Create a new report and provide access to the client.
2.Ensure the client can access all reported cases except Closed or Resolved cases.
3.If possible, include a date filter so the client can view cases based on recently reported dates.

Project Name: AU Finance AMC 2025-26
Account Name: AU Small Finance Bank Limited

Please check and let us know if any additional details are required from our end.

Regards
Lahu Gonde

mpr_subject: Requirement My Portal to Azure Sync Issue: Need to change the area path from customernext to Businessnext
details:
Please find the requirement IDs: 50591, 50627 which are raised by DSG team and not syncing to azure due to area path.

Please follow the below steps to solve this out:
Make the required changes to the below Business Enforcement Rules.
 
Requirement Object BER Name: Product type: CustomerNext
Case Object BER Name: Product Type-CustomerNext
 
Once this is completed, the following fields must be updated via a mass update for the object IDs mentioned above:
Azure Area Path (Requirement): Safe Portfolio 1\BusinessNext ART 1
Azure Failure Count (Requirement): 0
Azure Execution Status (Requirement): 0
Requirement Azure Execution Error Message: Clear this field (leave it empty)
subject: Requirement My Portal to Azure Sync Issue: Need to change the area path from customernext to Businessnext

mpr_subject: Support Root Cause Field Creation
details:
1. Create a new “Support Root Cause” field with given values. ( Reference Existing Field : Root cause )
2. Make this field mandatory for the Engineer – Production role ( Basis Status code as per existing field logic).
3. The Support Root Cause field should be visible only to the following roles:
Engr Production
(Applicable for both New and Details pages)
Customers (Applicable for Details page) - Keep the Display Name as Root Cause
4.The existing RCA Details field should be removed from the New/Edit pages for all the above roles.
5.The newly created field to be added in reports ( All Production Incidents Detailed Report - OEG )
6.Data to be migrated from 1st April'25 till date
subject: Support Root Cause Field Creation
